<TITLE> Tax-dodge verdict on former NBR member Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 18 (bdnews24.com)A special court has set Thursday for the verdict in a tax-dodge case against former NBR member ATM Sarwar Hossain. After hearing prosecution arguments, judge Amar Kumar Roy of the Special Judge Court-2 on the Sangsad Bhaban premises, Tuesday set the verdict date. Sarwar Hossain is evading arrest. On Aug 15, deputy commissioner of the National Board of Revenue Rabiul Hassan filed the tax evasion case against Sarwar with Dhaka senior special judge Md Azizul Haque's court. The case was later transferred to the special judge's court for trial. The case statement said the accused concealed information about Tk 4.32 crore in assets in 2000-2001 to 2006-2007 taxation years and dodged paying income tax. Charges were framed on Sept 13 and depositions were recorded until Sept 17. A total of five prosecution witnesses testified. bdnew
